articles.title: October BTO sales exercise applications 3 times the number of flats launched: Chee Hong Tat
articles.content: Applications for the October Build-To-Order (BTO) sales exercise have exceeded three times the number of flats launched, said Minister for National Development Chee Hong Tat. Despite being oversubscribed, the minister assured that many first-time applicants have a good chance of securing a flat. Chee stated that in order to meet the housing needs of seniors and singles, almost 3,000 2-room Flexi flats were offered during this exercise.
